<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,359,493]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,359,385]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
. Specimens of this species were not studied. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nielson, M. W." box="[796,968,359,385]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 318" refId="ref38619" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1982) A revision of the subfamily Coelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) IV. Coelidiini. Pacific Insects Monograph, 38, 1 - 318." type="journal article" year="1982">Nielson (1982)</bibRefCitation>
adequately described and illustrated the species based on specimens collected from Munnar and Tenmalai (
<collectingCountry box="[900,963,395,422]" name="India" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">India</collectingCountry>
). This species can be easily recognized by the piceous to deep fuscous coloration with a narrow flavous band along the forewing costa, and by the subapical processes on the aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[516,608,467,493]" captionStart="FIGURES 24" captionStartId="59.[151,264,1817,1842]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,223,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@59.[151,1436,181,1797]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 24 A–V. Species of Creberulidia Nielson and Hiatusorus Nielson, male genitalia. A–D. Creberulidia excelsa (Distant); E–H. C. pica (Nielson); I–L. C. quadrispinata (Nielson); M–Q. Hiatusorus concavus (Nielson); R–V. H. hardyi (Nielson). Modified and reproduced from Nielson 1982 (Figs. A–H, M–Q), Nielson 1991 (Figs. I–L) and Nielson 2015 (Figs. R–V)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366592/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs. 24</figureCitation>
G–H).
</paragraph>
